title: In Memory of Maestro, "The Buddha Kitty"
description: Maestro was the most special cat I have ever known. He was PURE LOVE. Never hissed, never scratched. Only meowed to tell me his food/water/litter needed attention. He loved belly rubs, cuddles, sitting and laying belly up in the sun. Always happy. Always loving. The minting of this NFT is to memorialize his spirit. To spread fragments of his unconditional love around the globe. Rest in peace Maestro. May your memory be eternal.

description: Made by Fernando Luiz, an Brazilian artist who is minimalist par excellence, Fernando Luiz is, above all, an interpreter. The line of the drawing, always highlighted, reveals its graphic vocation. The mark of his trajectory is a transparent diversity, which unmasks the non-conformity and the nature of an experimenter, resulting in a type of plural dialect. His favorite themes are cultures and religious archetypes, tribal graphics and forms of Nature.

title: Flat Noise Loop
description: Generative Art plot, made with Cinema4D and Axidraw. Pierre Paslier is a London-based generative artist. He graduated from the Royal College of Art in 2014. A heartfelt creator, he has been obsessed with drawing robots for the past few years. His work is mainly plotter based, experiencing the intersection between the physical and the digital. An active member of the vibrant generative local scene, he founded Generative Hut in 2019 as an anchor for the generative artistic community. He's always buying too many pens.

title: 2d 2 1d
description: Artist: Marcel Schwittlick (@schwittlick_) 2D21D (2014, processing edition) The project 2D21D (2 dimensions to 1 dimension) is a homage to Rene Magritte (Ceci n'est pas une pipe.) and a critique on the notion of the picture. Pictures, especially photographs, are a representation of subjects, not the subjects themselves. There is really a whole dimension of information and context, something that can not be reconstructed, missing from the subject, when looking at a representation of it. This work takes this loss one step further, and removes one more dimension from the photograph, bringing this to a level of perversion.

title: Odda - The curse
description: Odda is a former samurai from Ini Kingdom, whose anger was always the reason of its fame. At the age of 17, Odda executed a samurai within the sacred grove, because of that he was cursed by Ini's King, to be exhiled. The curse of Odda prevents him to use any kind of sword until his last breath. He carries a Tant√µ so that at the time of his death, He is able to commit a harakiri/seppuku and overcome its curse. Since then, odda lived in the outskirts of the forbidden pass, where he learned to hunt and live among the animals and beings of the grove. Many believe that Odda is no longer a human being, and that the rage consumed him and turned him into a entity that haunts the woods.

title: o11.1 ‚Äî Leave the darkness alone ‚Äî rev.01.1
description: On the way of spiritual emancipation, everyone has the right and the opportunity to go faster than others. On this road, there are no such obstacles as exist in the material world where there is dependence on each other.  At the same time, many forward-looking people are displeased. They do not understand that the fear of being late and the fear that someone is better than them makes them hurry. Those in a hurry become superficial and begin to make mistakes. Fear obscures the mind.

title: GAN Narratives- Telling the Truth, but Telling it Slant
description: I wrote a poem titled 'Creation', trying to capture 1 kind of creative process- eloquently put by Michelangelo as 'every stone block has a statue inside it and its upto the sculptor to set it free'. The poem I wrote is about a block of wood lying around, unattended to and gathering dust. One fine day a sculpture emerges from it- an artist saw that piece of wood and brought out the sculpture hidden in it. In my practice working with GANs, i feel there's a strong resemblance to creating art from the massive dump of the latent space. Putting all of this together, I use the BigGAN latent space to tell the story of the poem I wrote, searching through the latent space for appropriate visuals for each line of text, and interpolating between various frames to create the final video output. Finally paraphrasing Emily Dickinson's beautiful words, GANs try and replicate the truth of the dataset, but end up doing it in a 'slant' manner. Twitter- @harshitrnnh

title: GAN Narratives- Telling the Truth, but Telling it Slant
description: I wrote a poem titled 'Creation', trying to capture 1 kind of creative process- eloquently put by Michelangelo as 'every stone block has a statue inside it and its upto the sculptor to set it free'. The poem I wrote is about a block of wood lying around, unattended to and gathering dust. One fine day a sculpture emerges from it- an artist saw that piece of wood and brought out the sculpture hidden in it. In my practice working with GANs, i feel there's a strong resemblance to creating art from the massive dump of the latent space. Putting all of this together, I use the BigGAN latent space to tell the story of the poem I wrote, searching through the latent space for appropriate visuals for each line of text, and interpolating between various frames to create the final video output. Finally paraphrasing Emily Dickinson's beautiful words, GANs try and replicate the truth of the dataset, but end up doing it in a 'slant' manner. Twitter- @harshitrnnh

title: Meta ball
description: Generative Art plot, made with Cinema4D and Axidraw. Pierre Paslier is a London-based generative artist. He graduated from the Royal College of Art in 2014. A heartfelt creator, he has been obsessed with drawing robots for the past few years. His work is mainly plotter based, experiencing the intersection between the physical and the digital. An active member of the vibrant generative local scene, he founded Generative Hut in 2019 as an anchor for the generative artistic community. He's always buying too many pens.

title: WE_ARE_ALL_CONNECTED
description: WE_ARE_ALL_CONNECTED 12-03-2021 Living in cryptovalued, globalized, pandemic world is a completely new scenario. Our realm is being transformed from domestic to domesticated life and spaces of subversivity are running low.  Globalized world has been revealed as the perfect environment for new patogens agent to spread around the world, easily, cost free and fast.  As covid-19 spread around the world as our freedom decrease. In this completely new global environmet, physical stages of free trade, of information, hugs, chats, bodies, art pieces, food, knowledge, books, workforce are growing smaller.  Due to government restriction in favour of transparency and due to the big increase of cryptovalue market, even banknotes trading is becoming harder. But banknotes are the only good free to be exchanged, hand to hand, country by country, market by market, cashier‚Äôs desk by cashier‚Äôs desk.  The art piece ‚Äú	WE_ARE_ALL_CONNECTED‚Äù is configured as an art performance which highlights contemporary cryptovalued, globalized, pandemic world charachteristic.  I wrote on a 20‚Ç¨ banknote the message ‚Äú we are all connected‚Äù, the date of the release in the money circulation system and a dot on the europe map printed on the banknote which indicate the place it has been released.  Travelling around the world, the banknote, as a physical blockchain signature, will incorporate time and spatial coordinates of its passage, allowing new users to compare their current time and spatial coordinates.
